<div id="review_2245866564" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2245866564" />
    <a title="Ashley" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9516568-ashley"><img alt="Ashley" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1432037427p2/9516568.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2245866564?book_show_action=true">Jan 07, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ashley" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ashley" href="/user/show/9516568-ashley">Ashley</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2245866564" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8574194303968966986">It was difficult for me to settle on a 3 star rating. How can you rate an entire collection of different stories, all by different authors, using this system? It seems unfair. Ultimately, some of these fairy tales were wonderfully retold, others were just short of awful. The last couple stories were my favorite, with a special attachment to The Seven Stage a Comeback (a retelling of Snowhite and the Seven Dwarves). I also enjoyed Becoming Charise, Twelve Dancing Princesses, Hansel&apos;s Eyes, Instru</span>
  <span id="freeText8574194303968966986" style="display:none">It was difficult for me to settle on a 3 star rating. How can you rate an entire collection of different stories, all by different authors, using this system? It seems unfair. Ultimately, some of these fairy tales were wonderfully retold, others were just short of awful. The last couple stories were my favorite, with a special attachment to The Seven Stage a Comeback (a retelling of Snowhite and the Seven Dwarves). I also enjoyed Becoming Charise, Twelve Dancing Princesses, Hansel's Eyes, Instructions, and Mrs. Big: Jack and the Beanstalk Retold. Because the retellings I thoroughly enjoyed from beginning to end made up less than half the book (6 out of 13 stories/poems), I had to give the collection 3 stars.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8574194303968966986" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review2245866564">
  <td colspan="2">
    <div class="updateActionLinks">
        <a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link2245866564" title="Flag this review as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=2245866564&amp;resource_type=Review&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F819930.A_Wolf_at_the_Door">flag</a>





      <span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_review_2245866564'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it gr-button gr-button--small" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F819930.A_Wolf_at_the_Door">Like</a></span>
