    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2529420402" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2529420402" />
    <a title="Grace" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/86738413-grace"><img alt="Grace" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2529420402?book_show_action=true">Sep 13, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Grace" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Grace" href="/user/show/86738413-grace">Grace</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2529420402" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6116835989265732248">In my opinion this is a really good book. Maybe to some a bit childish but honestly i enjoyed it. Althogh 1 of the storys was a bit confusing at first. The storys are told in a way that you wouldn’t think about. And the ending isn’t always happy. In the end that’s what makes them in a way better then the traditional Disney storys. (Although they’re not the traditional storys) </span>

          </span>
        </div>


