<div id="review_3553299686" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3553299686" />
    <a title="Niki" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/44610496-niki"><img alt="Niki" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1574295818p2/44610496.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3553299686?book_show_action=true">Sep 17, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Niki" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Niki" href="/user/show/44610496-niki">Niki</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/44610496-niki?shelf=younger-years">younger-years</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3553299686" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3727063770374876042">I first came across this book when I was around ten or eleven. I remember being enchanted. Reread back in May, for the first time in probably 15 years. Was so, so pleasantly stunned to realize that my favorite-author-as-an-adult, Kelly Link, wrote one of the most memorable short stories in the collection. I think I blew through this in a day or two. The magic still holds up. &lt;3 </span>

          </span>
        </div>


